< """
< OpenAI-Compatible Chat Provider with Custom Headers Support
< 
< This module provides a custom chat model provider that extends langchain-ollama's
< ChatOllama to support OpenAI-compatible APIs (Ollama, Groq, etc.) with custom
< request headers, particularly for request ID tracking.
< 
< Key Features:
< - Works with any OpenAI-compatible API (Ollama, Groq, etc.)
< - Supports custom request ID headers (configurable via environment variable)
< - Compatible with LangGraph's init_chat_model via custom provider registration
< - Maintains full compatibility with langchain-ollama features
< 
< API Compatibility:
< - **Ollama**: Supports OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions endpoint
< - **Groq**: Fully OpenAI-compatible API at https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
<   (See: https://console.groq.com/docs/openai)
< 
< Usage:
<     # Via environment variables
<     export CUSTOM_LLM_BASE_URL="https://api.groq.com/openai/v1"
<     export CUSTOM_LLM_KEY="your-groq-api-key"
<     export CUSTOM_LLM_MODEL="gpt-oss:120b"
<     export CUSTOM_LLM_REQUEST_ID_HEADER="X-Request-ID"  # Optional, defaults to X-Request-ID
<     
<     # Direct instantiation with request_id from state
<     model = ChatOpenAICompatible(
<         model="gpt-oss:120b",
<         base_url="https://api.groq.com/openai/v1",
<         api_key="your-groq-api-key",
<         request_id=state.get("request_id"),  # Pass from LangGraph state
<         request_id_header="X-Request-ID"
<     )
<     
<     # With init_chat_model (requires provider registration)
<     model = init_chat_model(
<         model="gpt-oss:120b",
<         model_provider="openai_compatible",
<         base_url="https://api.groq.com/openai/v1",
<         api_key="your-groq-api-key",
<         request_id_header="X-Request-ID"
<     )
< 
< Request ID Tracking:
<     The provider includes a request ID in the custom header for each request.
<     Pass the request_id parameter (typically from your LangGraph state) to maintain
<     consistent tracking across your graph execution. If not provided, a UUID will
<     be generated at initialization time. This is useful for tracking requests across
<     distributed systems and debugging issues.
< """
